RUMOR: FEMA is confiscating property. If I apply for disaster assistance and my land is deemed unlivable, it will be seized.

FACT: FEMA cannot seize your property. Applying for disaster assistance does not grant the federal government authority or ownership of your property.

RUMOR: The FAA is restricting access to airspace for rescue and recovery operations.

FACT: The FAA is not restricting access for recovery operations. The FAA is coordinating closely with state and local officials to make sure everyone is operating safely.

RUMOR: FEMA only provides loans that must be paid back.

FACT: There are some less common situations in which you may have to pay FEMA back if you receive duplicate benefits from insurance or a grant from another source. But in most cases, FEMA grants do NOT have to be paid back.

RUMOR: FEMA will only provide $750 to survivors to support their recovery.

FACT: Totally false. This is called Serious Needs Assistance. It is an immediate payment to help cover essential items and emergency supplies while FEMA assesses your eligibility for additional funds.

I can think of few things more despicable than lying to Americans in need about the help available to them.
